Interface CommutativeMonoid<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the elements of the underlying set
    All Superinterfaces:

    public interface CommutativeMonoid<T>
extends CommutativeSemigroup<T>, Monoid<T>
    The algebraic structure of a commutative monoid (less common an 'abelian monoid'), meaning that the operation is commutative and associative.
